    {
        "content": "<p>Is it because, when you specify <code>monof</code>, it tries to skip ahead and fill in <code>a</code> and <code>b</code> too?</p>",
        "id": 501463409,
        "sender_full_name": "Chris Wong",
        "timestamp": 1740381765
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It might work if you mark <code>a b</code> as strict implicit parameters<br>\n<a href=\"https://lean-lang.org/doc/reference/latest//Terms/Functions/#implicit-functions\">https://lean-lang.org/doc/reference/latest//Terms/Functions/#implicit-functions</a></p>",
        "id": 501463708,
